Package ohos.agp.components.element

Class AnimatedStateElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.agp.components.element.Element
      • ohos.agp.components.element.ElementContainer
        • ohos.agp.components.element.StateElement
          • ohos.agp.components.element.AnimatedStateElement

  • public class AnimatedStateElement
extends StateElement
    Provides an Element object that can be changed based on the component state.

    An ElementContainer can contain multiple Element objects, but only one of them is valid. The validity is implemented by ComponentState.

    3

      • addStateTransition

        public void addStateTransition​(int[] fromStateSet,
                               int[] toStateSet,
                               Element element)
        Adds a pair of state set and Element object to a container.

        The state set and Element object always appear in pairs.

        Parameters:
        fromStateSet - Indicates the state set that specifies the start of the transition. It is represented by an array. A negative number in this array indicates a non-matching state. An empty array or the value 0 indicates a matched state.In general, the values of this array are obtained from ComponentState.
        toStateSet - Indicates the state set that specifies the end of the transition. It is represented by an array. A negative number indicates a non-matching state. An empty array or the value 0 indicates a matched state. In general, the values of this array are obtained from ComponentState.
        element - Indicates the Element object to display in the specified state set. Only an Element object that does not change with the state can be added.
        Since:
        3
